value.title: Supporters gather for Prayer vigil for Trump outside Walter Reed

value.title: Sanders to host socially distant rally for Biden in New Hampshire

value.excerpt: The Trump campaign has been hitting Nevada harder than ever this election season, and they seem certain the state might be President Trump’s for the taking this November.

value.excerpt: Murphy says Russia has a “clear desire to try to elect President Trump to a second term.”

value.title: Pelosi: Trump diagnosis 'tragic,' hopefully leads to 'saner approach' to pandemic
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi said that President Trump’s COVID-19 diagnosis is “tragic” and “very sad,” but predictable, given his frequent contact with crowds.

value.title: Boris Johnson wishes Trump 'speedy recovery' from COVID-19
value.excerpt: UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson wished President Trump a "speedy recovery" Friday, hours after he and First Lady Melania Trump tested positive for COVID-19.

value.excerpt: Rogers, 92, is an outspoken critic of President Trump and supporter of the Biden campaign.

value.title: Trump says he doesn't know who Proud Boys are, says 'let law enforcement do their work'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Wednesday tried to clear up confusion after telling the right-wing men’s group the Proud Boys to “stand back and stand by,” saying he didn’t know who the group was but they should let law enforcement do their job.

value.title: Chicago Mayor Lightfoot slams Trump after he blasts Windy City violence
value.excerpt: Democratic Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot fired back at President Trump on Tuesday night after he skewered her city during a presidential campaign debate against Joe Biden as a hotbed of crime and violence.

value.title: Biden says at debate he doesn't support Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it 'crucial framework'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden said Tuesday night at the first presidential debate that he does not support the Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it a “crucial framework” for meeting climate change challenges.

value.title: Former Playboy Playmate Karen McDougal says she’s ‘been forgiven by Jesus’ for alleged Trump affair
value.excerpt: During the 2016 election, National Enquirer parent company American Media Inc. paid McDougal $150,000 for the rights to her story, which it never published. The company eventually acknowledged the purchase was a “catch-and-kill” maneuver to boost Trump's presidential prospects.

value.title: Florida's top city for Cuban exiles goes to bat for GOP in 2020: 'Trump Town'
value.excerpt: The city of Hialeah, outside Miami, is known for its Cuban American community of working families, tight incomes and friendships among neighbors -- and as the election nears, many say they're leaning strongly toward voting for President Trump.

value.title: CNN’s Don Lemon suggests Trump was ‘hopped up’ on performance-enhancing drugs during debate
value.excerpt: CNN’s Don Lemon suggested that President Trump appeared to be “hopped up” on a performance-enhancing drug during Tuesday night’s presidential debate.

value.title: Could California’s policies work on a federal scale under a Biden-Harris administration?
value.excerpt: California has long been known for its push toward more progressive policies, many of which now form the basis of the Joe Biden-Kamala Harris presidential ticket. But whether or not such proposals have been successful – and whether California should be lauded as a model, is subject to debate.

value.title: Matt Gorman: Trump has a new running mate now
value.excerpt: Yes, Vice President Mike Pence is still around. And no, the near-constant chatter about former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley did not come to pass.
